---
description: Keep terrain collision, ALT, and rendered terrain aligned
alwaysApply: true
---

# Terrain Altitude Invariants

- Treat `worldY`, `terrainHeightAt(x, z)`, and `ALT` as separate values.
- `ALT` always means altitude above ground: `ALT = worldY - terrainHeightAt(x, z)`.
- Never use `position.y` directly as HUD altitude, flare height, landing height, or scoring altitude.
- Terrain collision, landing detection, HUD altitude, pause/debug snapshots, and scoring must all use the same shared terrain height source.
- On terrain contact, clamp `worldY` exactly to `terrainHeightAt(x, z)` and set `ALT` to exactly `0`.
- Prevent terrain penetration with sweep or substep collision checks when a single frame could tunnel through rising ground.
- Rendered terrain must use the same coordinate orientation and height source as collision terrain. A mirrored or remapped terrain mesh is a bug.

```ts
// ❌ Wrong
const altitude = state.position.y;
const hitGround = state.position.y <= 0;

// ✅ Correct
const terrainHeight = terrainHeightAt(state.position.x, state.position.z);
const altitude = state.position.y - terrainHeight;
const hitGround = altitude <= 0;
```
